value.title: Trump team removes members of Pentagon's Defense Policy Board, including Kissinger, Albright
value.excerpt: The Defense Department on Friday said that a number of members of its Defense Policy Board -- including former Secretaries of State Henry Kissinger and Madeleine Albright -- had been removed.

value.title: Exclusive: Former CIA station chief Darrell Blocker floated to lead agency under Biden, source says
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: While President-elect Joe Biden has yet to announce his pick for CIA director, an array of names has been highlighted, and among them is Darrell M. Blocker -- one of the highest-serving persons of color to have served in the clandestine service, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Trump's furniture fail: that's not a desk, Donald – it's a table for TV dinners
value.excerpt: The Resolute desk at the White House is made of timbers taken from a Royal Navy ship. It projects pure power. Is that why the defeated US president has switched to an occasional table he can barely squeeze his legs under?

value.title: ‘Betrayed’ Black asylum seekers say Trump administration is ramping up deportations by force and fraud
value.excerpt: ICE uses physical abuse, solitary confinement and false documents to force Black and African asylum seekers onto 'death planes,' The Times has found through interviews and legal documents.

value.title: Tulsi Gabbard urges Trump to grant clemency to Assange, Snowden
value.excerpt: U.S. Rep. Tulsi Gabbard has called on President Trump to pardon National Security Agency (NSA) whistleblower Edward Snowden and WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange before the president leaves office on Jan. 20, according to a report.

value.title: Trump's continued rhetoric over election hampers recovery as Americans face heightened economic and health fears
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump finally confirmed Thursday that he will vacate the White House in January after weeks of plunging America into a dark period of uncertainty—where the fate of democracy sometimes seemed to be hanging by a thread—but he largely ignored the mounting challenges his successor is facing

value.title: Angry Trump promises rally in battleground state of Georgia
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Thursday renewed baseless claims that “massive fraud” and crooked local officials in battleground states led to his election defeat, and said he’ll go to Georgia for a rally

value.title: Defund-police supporters tell Biden they're 'not going away'
value.excerpt: Far-left advocates of defunding the police say they are "not going away" just because Joe Biden won the presidency.

value.title: Trump administration removes experts from Defense Policy Board
value.excerpt: Several high profile members of the Defense Policy Board were removed on Wednesday by the Trump administration, in yet another purge of longstanding foreign policy experts and national security establishment figures in the final days of the Trump era, according to three defense officials.

value.title: Biden says family will have 'small group' around Thanksgiving table, urges Americans to sacrifice gatherings
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden called on Americans to make a sacrifice this Thanksgiving by foregoing large gatherings and noted that his own family is giving up their tradition to comply with coronavirus guidelines.

value.title: Dem leaders condemn Trump's pardon of Michael Flynn: 'Abuse of power'
value.excerpt: Democratic leaders lambasted President Trump for pardoning his former national security adviser Michael Flynn on Wednesday, condemning the move as a "brazen" abuse of power.

value.title: Up to the people, not the medical profession, to oust Trump: APA chief
value.excerpt: The public has had its say: President-elect Joe Biden’s margin of victory was by more than 6 million votes, and on Jan. 20, he will take office.

value.title: Joe and Jill Biden: Our most important Thanksgiving tradition
value.excerpt: This Thanksgiving, tables throughout our country will have an empty chair.

value.title: Trump campaign adviser Boris Epshteyn tests positive for coronavirus
value.excerpt: Boris Epshteyn, a campaign adviser to President Trump, announced Wednesday that he has tested positive for the novel coronavirus.

value.title: Progressive groups want 'squad member' Rashida Tlaib in Biden cabinet
value.excerpt: Progressive groups are pushing President-elect Joe Biden to include more candidates who lean further to the left than him in his cabinet, including a member of the “Squad,” as they seek influence over policymaking.

value.title: Flournoy gets progressive boost in Biden's search for Pentagon chief
value.excerpt: "We believe Michèle Flournoy is the best candidate for the job," a group of arms control veterans write in an open letter to Biden.

value.title: Biden says he'll push 'pathway to citizenship for over 11 million undocumented people' in first 100 days
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has committed to forging "a pathway to citizenship for over 11 million undocumented people in America" in the first 100 days of his administration.

value.title: Joe Biden says 'Let's be thankful for democracy' in message of unity – live
value.excerpt: Biden will speak in Wilmington as US records highest daily Covid deaths since May and 172,935 new cases

value.title: Chinese leader Xi Jinping congratulates Biden on winning election
value.excerpt: Chinese President Xi Jinping on Wednesday sent a congratulatory message to President-elect Joe Biden, more than two weeks after the Democratic candidate was projected the winner of the US presidential election.

value.title: Willie Brown demands Gavin Newsom replace Kamala Harris with a Black woman
value.excerpt: Willie Brown does not want Kamala Harris' Senate seat to go a Latino, stating, "Racial minorities should know they should not try to fill each other's vacancies."

value.title: Janet Yellen and Kamala Harris keep shattering glass ceilings – but global elite boys club remains
value.excerpt: Young, University of Massachusetts Amherst and Tuugi Chuluun, Loyola University Maryland (THE CONVERSATION) Janet Yellen may soon become the first woman to lead the Treasury Department, about six years after shattering another glass ceiling at the top of the Federal Reserve.

value.title: Matt Schlapp: Nevada allowing Trump team to present election fraud case 'a great step'
value.excerpt: Nevada is ready to hear the Trump campaign's case regarding illegal balloting allegations in Clark County, American Conservative Union chairman Matt Schlapp told “Hannity” Tuesday night.

value.title: Trump will soon leave the White House. How long before he stops dominating the conversation?
value.excerpt: Since then, Trump has dominated America’s attention. He has worked hard to make sure that’s the case, of course, littering social media with his thoughts and often seizing the reins of traditional media by leveraging his position.

value.title: Trump's America-first approach 'meant America alone', says Joe Biden – video
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says his presidency would not be 'a third Obama term' and that he would consider appointing a Republican

value.title: AOC, Ilhan Omar try to block 'deficit hawk' from Biden administration
value.excerpt: Squad members Reps. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y. and Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., are mounting a petition against Biden nominating his former chief of staff Bruce Reed, who they say is a “deficit hawk,” to a role within the incoming administration.
